article.headline: Northeastern 67, Central Conn. 53
article.story: NEW BRITAIN, Conn. (AP) -- Jose Juan Barea had 22 points, nine assists and eight rebounds to lead Northeastern past Brown 67-53 Friday night in the opening game of the Mohegan Sun Classic. The game was the season opener for both teams. Northeastern will take on Central Connecticut and Brown will play Birmingham-Southern on Saturday night. Northeastern (1-0) jumped out to an early 10-2 lead after 3-pointers by Aaron Davis and Bennet Davis. The Huskies continued to pour it on and led 20-7 with 10:28 to go in the first half. Both teams then struggled offensively the rest of the period, and Northeastern went into the break with a 32-22 lead. The Huskies opened the second half with a 17-6 burst in the first 7:10. But Brown (0-1) staged a comeback late in the game and pulled to within 61-49 on a 3-pointer by Mark MacDonald. Marcus Becker pulled Brown to within 61-53 with a fastbreak layup with just over two minutes remaining. Barea responded with a pair of free throws and Brown turned the ball over on the next possession as Northeastern sealed the victory. Luke Ruscoe led Brown with 11 points, and Damon Huffmans added 10. Aaron Davis finished the game with eight points for Northeastern, while Janon Cole had nine off the bench. It was the Huskies' first win over Brown since Jan. 25, 2000, and the first season-opening win for Northeastern in five years.
